import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { AppBar, Toolbar, Typography, Container, Grid, Card, CardContent, Button, Snackbar, Alert } from '@mui/material';
import Forecast from './components/Forecast';

function App() {
  const [alertOpen, setAlertOpen] = useState(false);

  return (
    <>
      <AppBar position="static">
        <Toolbar>
          <Typography variant="h6">Disease Forecast Dashboard</Typography>
        </Toolbar>
      </AppBar>
      <Container sx={{ marginTop: 4 }}>
        <Grid container spacing={3}>
          <Grid item xs={12} md={8}>
            <Card>
              <CardContent>
                <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom>Forecast Overview</Typography>
                <Forecast setAlertOpen={setAlertOpen} />
              </CardContent>
            </Card>
          </Grid>
          <Grid item xs={12} md={4}>
            <Card>
              <CardContent>
                <Typography variant="h6">Alerts & Notifications</Typography>
                <Button variant="contained" color="error" onClick={() => setAlertOpen(true)}>
                  Show Dengue Alert
                </Button>
              </CardContent>
            </Card>
          </Grid>
        </Grid>
      </Container>
      <Snackbar open={alertOpen} autoHideDuration={6000} onClose={() => setAlertOpen(false)}>
        <Alert severity="warning" sx={{ width: '100%' }}>
          High risk of dengue in Region X this month! Take precautions.
        </Alert>
      </Snackbar>
    </>
  );
}

export default App;
